(275, 2, '2009-11-12 19:31:52', 'World''s First Flying Machine with Enlou, and The Palace Flophouse', '$7 Cover!: Since their formation in 2007, World’s First Flying Machine has constantly been crowding onto stages too small for the sextet and the menagerie of instruments that accompany them. They’ve crammed themselves and their always enthusiastic fans into clubs, bars, vegan restaurants, dorms, elevators and even an Urban Outfitters. In a little over a year of performing, WFFM has opened for acclaimed acts including Black Mountain, Headlights, David Dondero, The Brunettes, Titus Andronicus, and Dark Meat. \r\r\r', '2009-11-12 18:00:00', 'Canopy Club', 'http://www.canopyclub.com', 'canopy, club, music'),
(276, 2, '2009-11-12 19:31:52', 'Family Groove Company with Mhondoro Rhythm Success and TBA', '$7 Cover!: Family Groove Company is a four piece band from Chicago that is turning heads and catching ears with a sound that is uncannily fresh, and live performances that simply envelop audiences in the fun, excitement and passion that the band radiates from the stage.\r\rFGC integrates the groove sensibility developed by funk/jazz crossover artists like Herbie Hancock and Medeski, Martin, and Wood, with thoughtful, tight song writing that takes cues from the likes of Steely Dan and the Beatles. The result? An infectious, fresh sound the band calls "groove informed jazz/rock". ', '2009-11-13 00:00:00', 'Canopy Club', 'http://www.canopyclub.com', 'canopy, club, music');
