(30, 2, '2009-11-12 19:31:59', 'Mayday Parade with There For Tomorrow, Dangerous Summer, and City Lights', '$13 In Advance!: “It’s definitely a release that should be included in your Summer play list and not buried under the other pop-punk releases this season.” \r---AbsolutePunk.net\r\r“The Florida pop-punks lead off their debut record, “A Lesson in Romantics,” with an emotionally charged song that starts softly, but builds up quickly to a vicariously thrilling, angry reminder that – contrary to popular belief- “girls make boys cry,” too.\r---NY Post,Maxine Sheen\r\r"Mayday Parade writes songs that bring out the addict in all of us. Their catchy pop vocals, slap-in-the-face lyrics and bright, uptempo melodies are enough to send you to rehab for OD''ing on their debut album, ''A Lesson in Romantics.''" \r---AOL Music PopEater Music Blog\r\r"''A Lesson in Romantics'' is hands down the best album to come out this year…!" \r---GirlsGonePunkblog.mtv.com\r\r“A Lesson in Romantics…I would say that its better than the last two albums Fall Out Boy wrote…fans of this style will eat Mayday Parade up; something that they’ll no doubt have to get used to as they climb the ladder.” \r---ThePlayList.net\r\r', '2009-12-07 18:00:00', 'Canopy Club', 'http://www.canopyclub.com', 'canopy, club, music', ''),
